[Caution should be in place in drawing conclusions about relative standings as there is definitely weekend/post-weekend artifact with key countries not submitting reports to WHO on numbers of cases in the past 24 hours: In Europe, Spain, France, Sweden, and Belarus did not report any new cases. In the Americas, the USA reported over 60 000 new cases. In Africa, Algeria reported over 1000 cases...

The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update:

- The Americas region reported 59.0% of the global newly reported cases and 67.7% of newly reported deaths for this 24-hour period, maintaining its dominance as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 8.3 million cases. The USA reported 42.6% of cases (63 968), Brazil 34.1% (51 147), Colombia 4.8% (7254), Mexico 4.5% (6751), Argentina 3.2% (4801), Peru 2.6% (3923), and Chile 1.5% (2198).

- The European region reported 6.8% of the global newly reported cases and 4.7% of the newly confirmed deaths globally. Russia reported 32.4% (5635 of the regional newly confirmed cases, followed by Kazakhstan 8.1% (1402), (Spain 0% (0)), Israel 6.9% (1199), Romania 6.4% (1120), Turkey 5.3% (927), Ukraine 4.6% (807), (France 0% (0)), the UK 4.3% (745), Uzbekistan 3.4% (594), Kyrgyzstan 2.8% (483), and Serbia 2.7% (467). Italy, while not reporting more than 300 new cases to WHO, has increased its 7-day average by 19.2% over the preceding 7-day period, a sign there are increases in transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 (calculated from the daily spreadsheet we maintain with data from http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5351&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto).

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 4.9% of the global newly reported cases and 8.2% of global newly reported fatalities. Iraq reported 19.9% (2459), of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Iran 18.9% (2333), Saudi Arabia 16.0% (1968), Pakistan 9.5% (1176), Oman 9.3% (1147), Morocco 5.1% (633), Egypt 3.9% (479), and Kuwait 3.8% (464). Pakistan is decreasing its daily case count steadily during the month of July 2020, while at the same time cases are increasing in Iraq and Oman. This region remains highly active, with multiple countries still in a surge mode.

- The African region reported 6.6% of the global newly reported cases and 3.5% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 67.2% (11 233) of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Algeria 7.2% (1198), Ethiopia 2.6% (720), Ghana 3.5% (586), Nigeria 3.3% (555), Madagascar 2.6% (429), and Cameroon 2.4% (402). Since the beginning of July 2020, South Africa has reported daily new case counts of greater than 10 000, 18 of the 27 days.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.5% of the global newly reported cases and 0.86% of global deaths. The Philippines reported 53.2% (2036) of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Japan 15.8% (607), Singapore 12.6% (481), Australia 11.8% (453), China 4.9% (189), and South Korea 0.65% (25).

- The South East Asia region reported 21.2% of the global newly reported cases and 15.1% of global deaths. India reported 92.6% (49 931) of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 4.2% (2275) and Indonesia 2.8% (1492). India continues to be the driving force of the dominance of this region.

Impression: The overall picture is basically the same. The ordering of the regions has the Americas having the highest disease load and newly confirmed cases on a daily basis followed by the South East Asia region, then Europe followed by the Eastern Mediterranean, followed by the Africa region and the Western Pacific region representing the lowest daily caseload of all the regions.

Figure 2. The epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 27 Jul 2020, at the source URL above is an excellent visual representation of the epidemic as described in the above text. - Mod.MPP]

